me Measured and Imagined, Jessica Maier explores the history of this genre—which merged the accuracy of scientific endeavor with the imaginative aspects of art—during the rise of Renaissance print culture. Through an exploration of works dating from the fifteenth to the eighteenth centuries, her book interweaves the story of the city portrait with that of Rome itself. Highly interdisciplinary and beautifully illustrated with nearly one hundred city portraits, Rome Measured and Imagined advances the scholarship on Renaissance Rome and print culture in fascinating ways.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aCartography -- Italy -- Rome. 0aCartography -- Italy -- Rome.;Rome (Italy) -- Maps.;Rome (Italy) -- Description and travel. 0aCartographyzItalyzRome. 0aRome (Italy) -- Description and travel. 0aRome (Italy) -- Maps. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  arome, maps, cartography, early modern, history, archeology, geography, nonfiction, 15th century, petrarch, ruins, city portrait, print culture, renaissance, italy, leon battista alberti, francesco rosselli, survey, raphael, antiquity, pictorials, leonardo bufalini, surveying, pirro ligorio, bartolomeo marliani, giovanni falda, matteo greuter, prospectus, painting, art, classicism, antonio tempesta, mario cartaro, dissemination, market, images, stefano du perac.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015z978311063872108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311069043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226127774423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226127774/original  a978-3-11-063872-1  DG and UP eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015